HEADWORD: Tartralic
<hw>Tar*tral"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Tartar</er> the chemical compound.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid obtained as a white
amorphous deliquescent substance, <chform>C8H10O11</chform>; -- called
also <altname>ditartaric</altname>, <altname>tartrilic</altname>, or
<altname>tartrylic acid</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

